</li>
<li id="cite_note-Olson-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Olson_5-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Olson_5-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Olson_5-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Olson_5-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFOlson2005" class="citation magazine cs1">Olson, Robert (January–February 2005). "The Rise of 'Radical Middle' Politics". <i><a href="/wiki/World_Future_Society" title="World Future Society">The Futurist</a></i>. Vol.&#160;39, no.&#160;1. Chicago, Illinois: <a href="/wiki/World_Future_Society" title="World Future Society">World Future Society</a>. pp.&#160;45–47.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Futurist&amp;rft.atitle=The+Rise+of+%27Radical+Middle%27+Politics&amp;rft.volume=39&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=45-47&amp;rft.date=2005-01%2F2005-02&amp;rft.aulast=Olson&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARadical+centrism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
