<li id="cite_note-Miller-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Miller_6-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Miller_6-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFMiller2003" class="citation book cs1">Miller, Matthew (2003). <i>The Two Percent Solution: Fixing America's Problems in Ways Liberals and Conservatives Can Love</i>. New York City: Public Affairs/<a href="/wiki/Perseus_Books_Group" title="Perseus Books Group">Perseus Books Group</a>. p.&#160;71. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-58648-158-2" title="Special:BookSources/978-1-58648-158-2"><bdi>978-1-58648-158-2</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Two+Percent+Solution%3A+Fixing+America%27s+Problems+in+Ways+Liberals+and+Conservatives+Can+Love&amp;rft.place=New+York+City&amp;rft.pages=71&amp;rft.pub=Public+Affairs%2FPerseus+Books+Group&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-58648-158-2&amp;rft.aulast=Miller&amp;rft.aufirst=Matthew&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARadical+centrism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
